I. The 7-Layer Framework
The OSI (Open Systems Interconnection) model is a conceptual framework used to understand how data moves across a network.
Troubleshooting Methodology
In DevOps, we troubleshoot "Bottom-Up."
​Physical/Link: Is the cable plugged in?
​Network: Can I ping the IP?
​Transport: Is the Port listening (ss -tuln)?
​Application: Is the service returning a 200 OK (curl)?
